(557, 'Love, Rosie', 'Since the moment they met at age 5, Rosie and Alex have been best friends, facing the highs and lows of growing up side by side. A fleeting shared moment, one missed opportunity, and the decisions that follow send their lives in completely different directions. As each navigates the complexities of life, love, and everything in between, they always find their way back to each other - but is it just friendship, or something more?', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500//rpD0t7DhzJVadnzgxSYrqljQTL2.jpg', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500//1NqH58OiJYKtLX6ysH09B86JYY2.jpg', 129, 2014),
(558, 'The Shadow in My Eye', 'On March 21st, 1945, the British Royal Air Force set out on a mission to bomb Gestapo''s headquarters in Copenhagen. The raid had fatal consequences as some of the bombers accidentally targeted a school and more than 120 people were killed, 86 of whom were children.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500//jCKvbH3a4V5IPoRAG85eDaniNqO.jpg', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500//6LtEzA3Umx9mc0lq1g8xOfluGPx.jpg', 122, 2021),
