(866, 'The Terminator', 'In the post-apocalyptic future, reigning tyrannical supercomputers teleport a cyborg assassin known as the "Terminator" back to 1984 to kill Sarah Connor, whose unborn son is destined to lead insurgents against 21st century mechanical hegemony. Meanwhile, the human-resistance movement dispatches a lone warrior to safeguard Sarah. Can he stop the virtually indestructible killing machine?', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500//hzXSE66v6KthZ8nPoLZmsi2G05j.jpg', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500//ahUaAgnkFu7QlBh5h4LCNeaSurV.jpg', 160, 1984),
